Former Congressman Louis Stokes has passed away, leaving behind an influential legacy. He was a founding member of the Congressional Black Caucus and the first African-American to represent Ohio in Congress. Stokes believed in fairness and equal opportunity for all Americans. Despite growing up in difficult circumstances, he became a champion for those less fortunate. He fought for better healthcare access in struggling communities and tirelessly advocated for the people of Ohio. Stokes leaves behind a lasting impact on the many young leaders he inspired. President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama offer their condolences to his loved ones.